
=Contextual Quote=

" “disparate impact,”: a once obscure legal theory that is now transforming our world. Any traditional standard of behavior or achievement that impedes exact racial proportionality in any enterprise is now presumed racist. Medical school admissions tests, expectations of scientific accomplishment in the award of research grants, the enforcement of the criminal law—all are under assault, because they have a “disparate impact” on underrepresented minorities. When Race Trumps Merit provides an alternative explanation for those racial disparities. It is large academic skills gaps that cause the lack of proportional representation in our most meritocratic organizations and large differences in criminal offending that account for the racially disproportionate prison population."

- Heather MacDonald [https://thinkspot.com/discourse/4Du8jj/post/heather-mac-donald/when-race-trumps-merit-how-the-pursuit-of-equity-sacrifices-excellence-destroys-beauty-and-threatens-lives/8dQtDo?]


